As Nigerians continue to protest sad activities of SARS operatives all over the country, a team of Special Anti-Robbery squad operatives have been caught on tape assaulting a boy and his mum in Edo state after he refused to handover his phone to them. This barbaric act happened today at ringroad, Oredo Local Government Edo State. The SARS officers was captured beating and assaulting the boy together with his mother. Incidents of SARS assault and harassment has become a regular occurrence, hence calls for the federal government to call the security agents to order. Watch the video below: Video of SARS operatives assaulting a boy with his mum, because of his refusal to handover his phone to them, at ringroad, oredo local govt,Edo state. A post shared by  Thenaijafame (@thenaijafame) on Aug 27, 2019 at 8:58am PDT Source PORT HARCOURT (Sundiata Post) - The Association of Rivers State Professionals (ARSP) has said it welcomed the ongoing actions by the Joint Task Force (JTF), the Nigeria Police and other security agencies to arrest the deteriorating security situation in Rivers State by undertaking robust pre-emptive raids on identified security dark… January 7, 2016 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Int’l Society for Civil Liberties & the Rule of Law (Intersociety) has described the 11 points Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) reform of Inspector General of Police (IGP) Ibrahim Idris as a charade, insisting that it contained nothing new from the usual. However, it… August 16, 2018 In "News" A dramatic scene played out today in Delta state as protesters and SARS operatives clashed over arrest of suspected internet fraudsters. It was gathered that the operatives stormed a street in Warri to arrest some suspected internet fraudsters otherwise known as yahoo boys. These angered some of the people living… July 19, 2019 In "Metro"